105 std::list<TomatoCoordinates> TomatoQueue::filtered(float x, float y, float z)
106 {
107  std::list<TomatoCoordinates> result;
108  TomatoCoordinates loc = {x, y, z, 0.0};
109  std::copy_if(queue_.begin(), queue_.end(), std::back_inserter(result), [this, &loc](TomatoCoordinates t)
110  { return pow(loc.x - t.x, 2) + pow(loc.y - t.y, 2) + pow(loc.z - t.z, 2) > 3; });
111  return result;
112 }

123 int TomatoQueue::GetReachableTomatoCount(float x, float y, float z, float armlength)
124 {
125  reachable_tomatoes_.clear();
126  for(auto tomato = queue_.begin(); tomato!=queue_.end(); ++tomato){
127  if(!tomato->is_picked && pow(tomato->x - x, 2) + pow(tomato->y - y, 2) + pow(tomato->z - z, 2) < pow(armlength+tomato->r, 2)){
128  reachable_tomatoes_.push_back(&(*tomato));
129  }
130  }
131  SortQueue(x, y, z);
132  return reachable_tomatoes_.size();
133 }

149 bool TomatoQueue::IsBasketFull(void)
150 {
151  if (picked_tomatoes_.size() >= basket_capacity_)
152  {
153  ROS_ERROR("Basket is full: %ld of %d Tomatoes in basket!", picked_tomatoes_.size(), basket_capacity_);
154  return true;
155  }
156 
157  if (picked_tomatoes_.size() < (basket_capacity_ - 2))
158  {
159  ROS_INFO("Currently %ld of %d tomatoes in Basket.", picked_tomatoes_.size(), basket_capacity_);
160  }
161  else
162  {
163  ROS_WARN("Currently %ld of %d tomatoes in Basket.", picked_tomatoes_.size(), basket_capacity_);
164  }
165 
166  return false;
167 }
